cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is about developing a movie recommendation model that takes into account the novelty-seeking trait of users. This falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The model also leverages demographic information about users, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the model's performance, which could fall under the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper is focused on improving user experience, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
